{{Quote|I had to actually get filmed, um, individually, each sequence, so it took about a hundred—hundred and one shots, and I had to eat, uh, tofu, bro. [&hellip;] It was tofu. It was terrible, man. I had never had tofu in my life, I'm used to boil up, brother [laughs] and, y'know, next thing I'm eating this white stuff, y'know, and a hundred and one times. And, um, by the end of it, the whole crew—the whole camera crew were cracking up.|Bodie Taylor on his role in ''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones''|<ref name="TheTemShow">{{WebCite|url=https://www.nzonscreen.com/title/the-tem-show-2005|text=The Tem Show - Star Wars (Episode)|archivedate=20230312190634}} (Archived episode of ''The Tem Show''. Bodie Taylor is featured in parts three, four and five).</ref>}}

'''Bodie Tihoi Huitoroa-Taylor'''<ref name="Instagram">{{Instagram|username=tuatoatanga|name=Bodie Taylor}}</ref>, also known as '''Bodie Wheke Taylor'''<ref name="Te Awamutu News">{{WebCite|url=https://www.teawamutunews.nz/2025/10/from-clone-to-tour-guide/|title=From clone to tour guide|work=Te Awamutu News|date=2025-10-30|author=Chris Gardner|archivedate=20251113205716}}</ref> (born [[1976]]),<ref name="SWNZ" /> is a [[Wikipedia:Māori people|Māori]] actor from [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]] who portrayed the [[Cloning|clones]] of [[Jango Fett]] when they were age-equivalent to his twenties during [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']]. He also portrayed an unhelmeted [[212th Attack Battalion]] [[clone trooper]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']]. Much like the other unhelmeted clones portrayed by [[Temuera Morrison]], Bodie wore a blue bodysuit which was later digitally replaced with computer-generated [[Clone trooper armor|clone armor]].

==Biography==
[[File:CloneCadetTeen-SWBC7.png|thumb|left|250px|Taylor as a Clone cadet]]
Before [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], Bodie Taylor had never acted on-screen.<ref name="TheTemShow" /> Prior to his role in ''Star Wars'', Bodie took part in a Māori cultural [[Wikipedia:Kapa haka|kapa haka]] stage production called ''Ahorangi 2000''. While performing in [[Wikipedia:Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton, New Zealand]], he and his co-performer, 11 year old Tupoutahi Winitana (the main protagonist of the production, and the son of the production's director/producer), were approached by [[Temuera Morrison]] and a casting director for [[Lucasfilm]] to audition as younger versions of the [[Clone trooper|clones]].<ref name="SWNZ" />

During their auditions, they were recorded and photographed posing menacingly with traditional Māori weapons, such as [[Wikipedia:Taiaha|taiaha]], and showing off the Māori martial art of [[Wikipedia:Mau rākau|Mau rākau]].<ref name="SWNZ" /><ref name="NZHerald1">{{WebCite|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/young-actor-says-no-to-skywalking/VCU72YRZKZDEUVC5WA6R7R45AQ/?c_id=6&objectid=143428|text=Young actor says no to Skywalking|author=Cleave, Louisa|date=2000-07-07|archivedate=20210307123528}}</ref> After the audition, they were both told that they had been selected to be in ''Attack of the Clones''.<ref name="SWNZ" /> Due to the filming schedule of ''Attack of the Clones'' conflicting with ''Ahorangi 2000''{{'s}} tour dates, Winitana's parents turned down his role in the film, with his role eventually being given to [[Daniel Logan]] instead. Taylor, however, was free to leave the production, as his role wasn't as prominent.<ref name="NZHerald1" />

After his time in ''Star Wars'', Taylor picked up a few film and television roles in New Zealand productions, one being the Māori Television show ''Bro-tour.com'' where he and his friend Mike Jonathan traveled the world and met with some of the prominent Māori figures living abroad, such as [[Rena Owen]].<ref name="TheTemShow" /><ref name="NZHerald2">{{WebCite|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/around-the-world-bro-style/7YX2WLNWJKLYSKIUBFLCTWU3FY|text=Around the world, bro style|author=Hill, Rebecca Barry|date=2006-11-20|archivedate=20230623094228}}</ref>

